All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
ComputerLab
Class derived from Room, acting as a specific type of Room.
Event
Class acting as an event with a name, a size, and start and end times.
LectureHall
Class derived from Room, acting as a specific type of Room.
Main
Main class showing a solution of a randomly generated problem.
Problem
Problem class that generates two lists with events and rooms, readying them for the Solution class.
Room
Abstract class acting as base for the LectureHall and ComputerLab classes.
Solution
Class implementing a greedy approach to solving the problem given by/generated by the Problem class.
Utils
Utility class for the Problem and Solution classes, created specifically for code cleanliness and decluttering of aforementioned classes.
